<taxonomicName id="ACEB99D26785E6DF2DEF60DDDB9C5B61" authorityName="Spegazzini" authorityYear="1881" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Hysteriaceae" genus="Rhytidhysteron" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Rhytidhysteron" order="Patellariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="76EC02AF827DF68E2CA8AC306BA6034A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Rhytidhysteron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by having greyish-green ascomata with greenish-grey to yellow epithecium in the presence of KOH, and large and wide ascospores (45-47 
<normalizedToken id="310628F1626C7DCF00936769FFB4A0EF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
17-19 
<normalizedToken id="7DE76CA662A0155B891C743483FAAD22" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
